title: S. Jersey Boys: S.J. boys: Eastern edges Timber Creek in soccer
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Tri-County Diamond. Shaun Dowdy registered an assist and 10 saves as Glassboro blanked Cumberland, 2-0, at home. Sefa Gocmez and Durson Ortak scored.
Coaches Tournament. Unbeaten Washington Township earned the No. 1 seed in the South Jersey Coaches Association Tournament. The Minutemen will host No. 16 West Deptford on Saturday. First-round play begins Thursday. Football Junior running back Quran Dozier carried four times for 118 yards and two touchdowns to lead No. 7 West Deptford to a 62-0 victory over Sterling at Gateway.
David Hamilton opened scoring for the Eagles with a 67-yard run on the second play of the game. 
Gio Gismondi and Nick Diaco ran for touchdowns of six and 36 yards, respectively, in the third quarter to put the game out of reach. 
The game was rescheduled from Friday because of thunderstorms.
